item.title: Error_game_Js5Connect
item.dc:creator: @Arrav Arrav
item.description:
@Arrav wrote:

CoderOops:

Search bar… Google… LIKE CMON! This is asked 10times/day…

Stop spamming for postcount++, this is the help section, for those who need help and can’t find it. Let me count how many times I’ve seen it today… Lets see… 1… 2… wait nvm just 1.

If you’re getting the client error “error js6connect”; It is either a few reasons…

  1. Client cannot connect to the server (Ofc but the Server MUST be running FIRST before running the client) or else you will not be able to use the client.

  2. Client deob is broken or has an anti leech.

  3. Server has an Antileech, making the client not able to connect to the server.

  4. You haven’t ran the server before you connected to the client.

Error Js5Connect is a common client error that had started around the revisions 450+ or 500+ Revisions. So of course this won’t happen in a 317 or 377.
